Actress Zola Nomboma is joining other local celebrities who have launched their own underwear and shapewear ranges. Zola wrote on social media that she is excited about her long-awaited dream finally seeing fruition. She shared a picture of her dream come true and said it was a physical manifestation of her dreams and hard work. “I can finally introduce you guys to this dream of mine that I have worked so hard to make a reality. We’re a movement that celebrates bodies in all shapes and sizes while prioritising good quality, great functionality, and comfort,” she wrote. Zola added that her shop, lxvelove, would open online on Wednesday at 8am, where they would also launch the website.   For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.